In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water, and a
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low
simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For perfect timing, start cooking chicken and veggies when rice has 10 minutes left!

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Halve, core,
and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Quarter @lemon{1}. Mince
@cilantro{1/4%oz}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4.5%tbsp}, cilantro, and juice from
two lemon wedges. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a
drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Open package of @diced chicken thighs{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add chicken, onion, and bell pepper in a single layer; season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Add @savory paprika blend{1%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
and @dried oregano{1%tsp}; stir to combine. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until veggies are browned and chicken is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide between shallow #bowls{}. Top with chicken
and veggies. Drizzle with crema and serve with remaining lemon wedges on
the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.